<article xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" specific-use="sps-1.4" dtd-version="1.0" xml:lang="pt" article-type="research-article"><front><journal-meta><journal-id journal-id-type="publisher-id">ln</journal-id><journal-title-group><journal-title>Lua Nova: Revista de Cultura e Política</journal-title><abbrev-journal-title abbrev-type="publisher">Lua Nova</abbrev-journal-title></journal-title-group><issn pub-type="ppub">0102-6445</issn><issn pub-type="epub">1807-0175</issn><publisher><publisher-name>CEDEC</publisher-name><publisher-loc>São Paulo, SP, Brazil</publisher-loc></publisher></journal-meta><article-meta><article-id pub-id-type="publisher-id" specific-use="scielo-v2">S0102-64452018000300003</article-id><article-id pub-id-type="publisher-id" specific-use="scielo-v1">S0102-6445(18)00010500003</article-id><article-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1590/0102-047080/105</article-id><article-categories><subj-group subj-group-type="heading"><subject>DOSSIÊ - MOVIMENTOS SOCIAIS, ESTADO E POLÍTICAS PÚBLICAS: ABORDAGENS E CASOS</subject></subj-group></article-categories><title-group><article-title>AS ORIGENS MOVIMENTISTAS DE POLÍTICAS PÚBLICAS: PROPOSTA ANALÍTICA APLICADA ÀS ÁREAS DE CRIANÇA E ADOLESCENTE, DIREITOS HUMANOS E SAÚDE</article-title><trans-title-group xml:lang="en"><trans-title>PUBLIC POLICIES AND THEIR ORIGINS IN SOCIAL MOVEMENTS: AN ANALYTICAL PROPOSAL APPLIED TO CHILDREN AND ADOLESCENTS, HUMAN RIGHTS AND HEALTH</trans-title></trans-title-group></title-group><contrib-group><contrib contrib-type="author"><contrib-id contrib-id-type="orcid">0000-0002-1845-046X</contrib-id><name><surname>Dowbor</surname><given-names>Monika</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff1"/></contrib><contrib contrib-type="author"><contrib-id contrib-id-type="orcid">0000-0003-0553-2746</contrib-id><name><surname>Carlos</surname><given-names>Euzeneia</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff2"/></contrib><contrib contrib-type="author"><contrib-id contrib-id-type="orcid">0000-0003-3026-3429</contrib-id><name><surname>Albuquerque</surname><given-names>Maria do Carmo</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff3"/></contrib></contrib-group><aff id="aff1"><addr-line><named-content content-type="city">São Leopoldo</named-content><named-content content-type="state">Rio Grande do Sul</named-content></addr-line><institution content-type="orgname">Universidade do Vale do Rio dos Sinos</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Departamento de Ciências Sociais </institution><country country="BR">Brazil</country><email>mdowbor@gmail.com</email></aff><aff id="aff2"><addr-line><named-content content-type="city">Vitória</named-content><named-content content-type="state">Espírito Santo</named-content></addr-line><institution content-type="orgname">Universidade Federal do Espírito Santo</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Departamento de Ciências Sociais </institution><country country="BR">Brazil</country><email>euzeneiacarlos@gmail.com</email></aff><aff id="aff3"><addr-line><named-content content-type="city">São Paulo</named-content><named-content content-type="state">São Paulo</named-content></addr-line><institution content-type="orgname">Centro Brasileiro de Análise e Planejamento</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Núcleo Democracia e Ação Coletiva </institution><country country="BR">Brazil</country><email>mcarmoa@gmail.com</email></aff><pub-date pub-type="epub-ppub"><month>09</month><year>2018</year></pub-date><issue>105</issue><fpage>47</fpage><lpage>80</lpage><history><date date-type="received"><day>18</day><month>05</month><year>2018</year></date><date date-type="accepted"><day>10</day><month>10</month><year>2018</year></date></history><permissions><license license-type="open-access" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" xml:lang="en"><license-p>This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.</license-p></license></permissions><abstract><p>Resumo Quem elabora as políticas públicas? Segundo a literatura sobre o tema, são os gestores públicos, as comunidades epistêmicas e de especialistas. Na fronteira entre esse campo e o de movimentos sociais, postulamos neste artigo que os movimentos não são apenas desafiadores do status quo, mas também podem ser propositores de alternativas para as políticas públicas. São discutidas e articuladas três categorias analíticas: inovação social, alternativa e instrumento de política pública, que ajudam a iluminar a atuação de movimentos que buscam transformar seus objetivos políticos em políticas públicas. Em seguida, aplicamos esse esquema analítico a três movimentos sociais - o de criança e adolescente, o de direitos humanos e o movimento sanitarista. Procuramos mostrar como a articulação desses três conceitos contribui para a reconstrução do processo que remete às origens movimentistas de políticas públicas.</p></abstract><trans-abstract xml:lang="en"><p>Abstract Who designs public policies? The public policy literature indicates that its producers are public administrators as well as epistemic and specialists communities. On the limits between this field and social movements, this article postulates that these movements are not only challengers of the status quo, but can also be proponents of alternatives to public policies. For such, it discusses and articulates three analytical categories: social innovation, alternative, and public policy instrument, which helps to clarify the actions of movements that seeks to transform their political objectives into public policies. Next, we apply this analytical scheme to three social movements - the children and adolescents movement, the human rights movement and the health movement. We show how the articulation between these three concepts contributes to the reconstruction of the process referring to social movement’s origins of public policies.</p></trans-abstract><kwd-group xml:lang="pt" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>Movimento Social</kwd><kwd>Política Pública</kwd><kwd>Instrumento</kwd><kwd>Alternativa</kwd><kwd>Inovação Social</kwd></kwd-group><kwd-group xml:lang="en" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>Social Movement</kwd><kwd>Public Policy</kwd><kwd>Instrument</kwd><kwd>Alternative</kwd><kwd>Social Innovation</kwd></kwd-group><counts><fig-count count="0"/><table-count count="0"/><equation-count count="0"/><ref-count count="35"/><page-count count="34"/></counts></article-meta></front><back><ref-list><ref id="B1"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><article-title>Repertórios de interação Estado-sociedade em um Estado heterogêneo: a experiência da era Lula</article-title><source>Dados</source><date><year>2014</year></date><fpage>325</fpage><lpage>357</lpage><issue>2</issue><volume>57</volume><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>ABERS</surname><given-names>Rebecca Neaera</given-names></name><name><surname>SERAFIM</surname><given-names>Lizandra</given-names></name><name><surname>TATAGIBA</surname><given-names>Luciana Ferreira</given-names></name></person-group></element-citation></ref><ref id="B2"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><article-title>Entrevista concedida</article-title><source>Olho Mágico</source><date><year>2001</year></date><issue>2</issue><volume>8</volume><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>ALMEIDA</surname><given-names>Márcio José</given-names></name></person-group><comment>Disponível em: https://bit.ly/2CV4dAR</comment></element-citation></ref><ref id="B3"><element-citation publication-type="book"><source>A rede Unida e o movimento de mudança na formação dos profissionais de saúde</source><date><year>2006</year></date><fpage>108</fpage><lpage>108</lpage><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>BARBIERI</surname><given-names>Fernanda Bersanetti</given-names></name></person-group><comment>Mestrado</comment></element-citation></ref><ref id="B4"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><